    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-14T08:40:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-14T08:40:00-05:00" n="351"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1447.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-14T09:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1914, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Báez desires more money, as he told Controller, in order to leave
                    office without adding to debt. Jimenistas desirous United States should place
                    itself on record acknowledging elections as soon as possible, so as to abate
                    pretensions Horacistas. If Provisional President should promulgate law
                    establishing functions financial expert and accepting Controller’s new budget,
                    then if Jiménez and Velásquez were to be pledged in writing to support as
                    condition precedent to recognition Controller legislation and turn over
                    collection of internal revenue to Receivership, all Dominican receipts and
                    disbursements would be controlled. Johnston’s new budget will provide for
                    repayment $250,000 yearly public works money, and $500,000 which fully redeems
                    internal revenue taxes. To retire Báez December 1st, without giving
                    administration additional floating debt, would cost, says Johnston, $70,000
                    extra; Johnston and myself consider outlay was already worth while. President
                    seemed receptive to idea.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
